    public static final String Gal_5_5 = "For we through the Spirit wait for the hope of righteousness by faith. ";
    public static final String Gal_5_6 = "For in Jesus Christ neither circumcision availeth any thing, nor uncircumcision; but faith which worketh by love. ";
    public static final String Gal_5_7 = "Ye did run well; who did hinder you that ye should not obey the truth? ";
    public static final String Gal_5_8 = "This persuasion [cometh] not of him that calleth you. ";
    public static final String Gal_5_9 = "A little leaven leaveneth the whole lump. ";
    public static final String Gal_5_10 = "I have confidence in you through the Lord, that ye will be none otherwise minded: but he that troubleth you shall bear his judgment, whosoever he be. ";
    public static final String Gal_5_11 = "And I, brethren, if I yet preach circumcision, why do I yet suffer persecution? then is the offence of the cross ceased. ";
    public static final String Gal_5_12 = "I would they were even cut off which trouble you. ";
    public static final String Gal_5_13 = "For, brethren, ye have been called unto liberty; only [use] not liberty for an occasion to the flesh, but by love serve one another. ";
    public static final String Gal_5_14 = "For all the law is fulfilled in one word, [even] in this; Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself. ";
    public static final String Gal_5_15 = "But if ye bite and devour one another, take heed that ye be not consumed one of another. ";
    public static final String Gal_5_16 = "[This] I say then, Walk in the Spirit, and ye shall not fulfil the lust of the flesh. ";
    public static final String Gal_5_17 = "For the flesh lusteth against the Spirit, and the Spirit against the flesh: and these are contrary the one to the other: so that ye cannot do the things that ye would. ";
    public static final String Gal_5_18 = "But if ye be led of the Spirit, ye are not under the law. ";
    public static final String Gal_5_19 = "Now the works of the flesh are manifest, which are [these;] Adultery, fornication, uncleanness, lasciviousness, ";
